HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 879
By Lamberth
A RESOLUTION to confirm the appointment of Mike Frick to the
heritage conservation trust fund board of
trustees.
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 11-7-104(a), provides for the creation
of the heritage conservation trust fund board of trustees; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 11-7-104(b), provides that the
governor shall appoint eleven members to the board; and
WHEREAS, Governor Bill Lee has appointed Mike Frick as a member of the heritage
conservation trust fund board of trustees representing West Tennessee to a term that will expire
on October 31, 2029; and
WHEREAS, Mike Frick is the retired Bank of America President for the Memphis market;
during his forty-one-year career at Bank of America, he also served as Global Commercial
Banking Market Executive; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Frick gives back to his community through his involvement with Central
Gardens Neighborhood Association (President), City of Memphis and Shelby County
Community Redevelopment Agency (Chair), Community LIFT (founding board member), and
Economic Club of Memphis (President); and
WHEREAS, Mr. Frick is a graduate of Rhodes College with a Bachelor of Arts degree in
International Studies; and
WHEREAS, Mike Frick is a person of integrity and an active citizen whose benevolence,
acumen, and strong commitment to public service have helped to enhance the well-being of this
State and its citizens; and
HJR0879
011607
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 11-7-104(b)(2), provides that each
member appointed by the governor to the heritage conservation trust fund board of trustees
shall be confirmed by joint resolution of the general assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that this body confirms the appointment of Mike Frick to the heritage
conservation trust fund board of trustees for a term that will expire on October 31, 2029.
